Abdomen
. Tergite 8 with posterior margin somewhat truncate; sternite 8 with posterior margin rounded and weakly pigmented (
Fig. 52
); tergite 9 with short ventral struts; sternite 9 with posterior margin truncate and with two pairs of long setae, the internal longest; tergite 10 at posterior margin emarginate, with short fringes and four setae on each side (
Fig. 56
). Median lobe of aedeagus with apex rounded in ventral view; curved shape and apex straight in lateral view (
Figs. 61–62
).
